This paper deals with lifted inference in probabilistic graphical models, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of permutations and MCMC methods for inference suggests that this paper could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also deals with computational linguistics (cs.CL) in the sense that it discusses the use of permutations to identify symmetries in a domain. Finally, the use of block partitions to identify symmetries suggests that this paper could also be categorized under control systems (cs.SY).
